hpnsaScsiMibRevMajor.name: hpnsaScsiMibRevMajor
hpnsaScsiMibRevMajor.description: The major revision level of the MIB. A change in the major revision level represents a major change in the architecture or functions of the MIB.

hpnsaScsiMibRevMinor.name: hpnsaScsiMibRevMinor
hpnsaScsiMibRevMinor.description: The minor revision level of the MIB. A change in the minor revision level may represent some minor additional support, no changes to any pre-existing information has occurred.

hpnsaScsiAgentModuleTable.name: hpnsaScsiAgentModuleTable
hpnsaScsiAgentModuleTable.description: A table of SNMP Agents that satisfy request pertaining to this MIB.

hpnsaScsiAgentModuleEntry.name: hpnsaScsiAgentModuleEntry
hpnsaScsiAgentModuleEntry.description: A description of the Agents that access system information.

hpnsaScsiAgentModuleIndex.name: hpnsaScsiAgentModuleIndex
hpnsaScsiAgentModuleIndex.description: A unique index for this module description.

hpnsaScsiAgentModuleVersion.name: hpnsaScsiAgentModuleVersion
hpnsaScsiAgentModuleVersion.description: The module version in XX.YY format. Where XX is the major version number and YY is the minor version number. This field will be a null (size 0) string if the agent cannot provide the module version.

hpnsaScsiAgentModuleDate.name: hpnsaScsiAgentModuleDate
hpnsaScsiAgentModuleDate.description: The module date. field octets contents range _________________________________________________ 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minute 0..59 6 7 second 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) This field will be set to year = 0 if the agent cannot provide the module date. The hour, minute, and second field will be set to zero (0) if they are not relevant. The year field is set with the most significant octet first.

hpnsaScsiHbaTable.name: hpnsaScsiHbaTable
hpnsaScsiHbaTable.description: A list of SCSI Host Bus Adapter entries.

hpnsaScsiHbaEntry.name: hpnsaScsiHbaEntry
hpnsaScsiHbaEntry.description: A description of an SCSI device/function.

hpnsaScsiHbaIndex.name: hpnsaScsiHbaIndex
hpnsaScsiHbaIndex.description: The SCSI HBA number that this entry describes.

hpnsaScsiHbaTargetId.name: hpnsaScsiHbaTargetId
hpnsaScsiHbaTargetId.description: The SCSI target ID or SCSI address for this HBA.

hpnsaScsiHbaManagerId.name: hpnsaScsiHbaManagerId
hpnsaScsiHbaManagerId.description: String that describes the SCSI Manager.

hpnsaScsiHbaHostAdapterId.name: hpnsaScsiHbaHostAdapterId
hpnsaScsiHbaHostAdapterId.description: String that describes the SCSI host adapter.

hpnsaScsiDevTable.name: hpnsaScsiDevTable
hpnsaScsiDevTable.description: A list of SCSI device entries.

hpnsaScsiDevEntry.name: hpnsaScsiDevEntry
hpnsaScsiDevEntry.description: A description of a SCSI device.

hpnsaScsiDevHbaIndex.name: hpnsaScsiDevHbaIndex
hpnsaScsiDevHbaIndex.description: The SCSI HBA number that this entry describes.

hpnsaScsiDevTargIdIndex.name: hpnsaScsiDevTargIdIndex
hpnsaScsiDevTargIdIndex.description: The SCSI target ID or SCSI address for this HBA.

hpnsaScsiDevLunIndex.name: hpnsaScsiDevLunIndex
hpnsaScsiDevLunIndex.description: The SCSI LUN for this HBA.

hpnsaScsiDevType.name: hpnsaScsiDevType
hpnsaScsiDevType.description: Identifies the type of SCSI device: Code Description ---- ----------- 00h Direct-access device (e.g. magnetic disk) 01h Sequential-access device (e.g. magnetic tape) 02h Printer device 03h Processor device 04h Write-once read-multiple device (e.g. some optical disks) 05h CD-ROM device 06h Scanner device 07h Optical Memory device (e.g. some optical disks) 08h Medium Changer device (e.g. jukeboxes) 09h Communications device 0A-1Eh Reserved 1Fh Unknown or no device type

hpnsaScsiDevRmb.name: hpnsaScsiDevRmb
hpnsaScsiDevRmb.description: Identifies whether the medium is removable or not. 0 = medium is not removable 1 = medium is removable

hpnsaScsiDevAnsiVer.name: hpnsaScsiDevAnsiVer
hpnsaScsiDevAnsiVer.description: Indicates the implemented ANSI version of this device. 0 = might or might not comply to an ANSI standard 1 = complies to ANSI X3.131-1986 (SCSI-1) 2 = comples to ANSI ?????? (SCSI-II) 3-7 = reserved

hpnsaScsiDevEcmaVer.name: hpnsaScsiDevEcmaVer
hpnsaScsiDevEcmaVer.description: Indicates the implemented ECMA version of this device. Zero code indicates that this device does not comply with this standard.

hpnsaScsiDevIsoVer.name: hpnsaScsiDevIsoVer
hpnsaScsiDevIsoVer.description: Indicates the implemented ISO version of this device. Zero code indicates that this device does not comply with this standard.

hpnsaScsiDevVendorId.name: hpnsaScsiDevVendorId
hpnsaScsiDevVendorId.description: Identifies the vendor of the product.

hpnsaScsiDevProductId.name: hpnsaScsiDevProductId
hpnsaScsiDevProductId.description: Identifies the product as defined by the vendor.

hpnsaScsiDevLogicalBlocks.name: hpnsaScsiDevLogicalBlocks
hpnsaScsiDevLogicalBlocks.description: A 32-bit value that represents the total number of logical blocks for this device. Octet 1 is the LSB, and octet 4 is the MSB.

hpnsaScsiDevBlockLength.name: hpnsaScsiDevBlockLength
hpnsaScsiDevBlockLength.description: A 32-bit value that represents the size of a logical block for this device. Octet 1 is the LSB, and octet 4 is the MSB.

hpnsaScsiDevCapacity.name: hpnsaScsiDevCapacity
hpnsaScsiDevCapacity.description: A value that represents the capacity of the device in megabytes. One megabyte equals to 1,048,576 when calculating this value.
